item.title: Need help! (srry if in wrong spot!)
item.dc:creator: @Mopar_Helper Mopar Helper
item.description:
@Mopar_Helper wrote:

From hamachi.cc Hamachi is a zero-configuration virtual private networking (VPN) application.

In other words Hamachi is a program that allows you to arrange multiple computers into their own secure network just as if they were connected by a physical network cable.


As it says its a virtual private networking (VPN) Application.
how does that make it anything to do with moparscape?
Hamachi can be used for other things too.
it wasnt created for moparscape, it was just an easier way of private networking.
